Package it.unive.lisa.cfg.type

Interface Type

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ArrayType, BooleanType, NumericType, PointerType, StringType
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BoolType, IntType, NullType, StringType, Untyped, VoidType
    public interface Type
    Type interface. Any instance of a concrete type, instance of Type, should be unique and implemented following the singleton design pattern (see for instance Untyped class).
